        <p> 
          Zuluk is a picturesque village located in the Pakyong district of East Sikkim, India, nestled at an altitude of around 10,000 feet. Known for its breathtaking views of the Eastern Himalayas, including the majestic Kanchenjunga, Zuluk offers an enchanting landscape with lush greenery, rolling hills, and winding roads that zigzag through the mountains. The village is famous for its unique, serpentine roads known as the "Old Silk Route," which were historically used for trade between India and Tibet. Zuluk is a popular destination for trekkers and nature lovers, offering a peaceful retreat, bird watching opportunities, and a chance to explore the cultural heritage of the region.





